The paper discusses learning-to-learn or meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The benchmarks used in the paper are image-based, indicating a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the handling of latent distribution shift, which is a common problem in neural networks and falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
